      "updated": 1774011499024,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Resource server invokes end points of\nauthentication server to validate\nvarious part of the token",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 68,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Resource server invokes end points of\nauthentication server to validate\nvarious part of the token",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "zRzAFGpKqRu5iSnbus61M",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 306,
      "y": 928,
      "width": 1234.458984375,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1204701524,
      "version": 497,
      "versionNonce": 140561004,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1774011838568,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Earlier to JWT we had sessionId(or JsessionID), there we had DB in Authentication server which well create the sessionId.\nSessionId contains sessionid, expirytime, userid and role. In cookies client will pass this jsessionId to resource server.\nResource server will then check its DB and check roles and other validation and send response.\nMajor issue in this is every time we hit server it used to check DB increasing latency, this is stateful.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 118,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Earlier to JWT we had sessionId(or JsessionID), there we had DB in Authentication server which well create the sessionId.\nSessionId contains sessionid, expirytime, userid and role. In cookies client will pass this jsessionId to resource server.\nResource server will then check its DB and check roles and other validation and send response.\nMajor issue in this is every time we hit server it used to check DB increasing latency, this is stateful.\n",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "c7TdUSgSBzIj8GFR6MYIw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 624,
      "y": 1085,
      "width": 207.1798553466797,
